import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['size'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['size'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['size'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of size?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['parent'], data['size'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between parent and size?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Parent')
    plt.ylabel('Size')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    name_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What are the most common names in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend([f'Total Names: {len(name_counts)}'])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['id'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['id'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['id'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['id'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['id'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xlabel('id')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of id?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
